body:
In regressions of cases from the SystemVerilog LRM, legal case on 1800-2012 page 695 (or 1800-2023 page 764-765) errors out:

%Error: syntax error, unexpected '[', expecting '.' or '='
    |       defparam somename[i].my_flop.xyz = i ;
|                         ^

**Code:**
```
module flop(input a,b, output c);
  parameter xyz = 0;
endmodule

module sv12_lrm_p0695_module_m1_a;
  genvar i;
logic [7:0] in,in1,out1;
  generate
    for (i = 0; i < 8; i = i + 1) begin : somename
      flop my_flop(in[i], in1[i], out1[i]);
      defparam somename[i].my_flop.xyz = i ;
    end
  endgenerate
endmodule
```

**Version:**
5.044

**Environment:**
Centos 7.9，GCC 11.5

